@prameshgautam please see the instructions at https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph#training . Specifically, 

> you have a directory containing training data files in npz (numpy) format. It's assumed that each npz file in your data folder has a vol parameter, which points to the numpy image data to be registered, [...]. It's also assumed that the shape of all image data in a directory is consistent.

We actually support many more formats, @ahoopes  can comment on that, but essentially having a folder with npz files is the easiest way to start.

@adalca got it thank you. I tried running training code with just one image in datadir with **vol** parameter in npz file.
I run the script using command `python scripts/torch/train.py data-dir/`. Same image is passed as fixed and moving image to the model in [https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph/blob/master/scripts/torch/train.py#L158](https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph/blob/master/scripts/torch/train.py#L158).

My question is how to arrange fixed and moving image for scan-to-scan registration. What is the correct way to pass moving and fixed image pair for training? I cannot find that info in README.
